WEBVTT

00:06.740 --> 00:08.318
Alright, y'all.

00:08.342 --> 00:10.857
Last time you saw me,
I had a bullet in my head.

00:10.881 --> 00:13.878
What had happened was
shit got crazy in Palmghetto.

00:18.152 --> 00:20.597
Bryce and Jenn bounced to Tampa.

00:20.621 --> 00:21.998
You really out, huh?

00:22.022 --> 00:24.467
I'ma be so squeaky clean up in Tampa.

00:24.491 --> 00:27.014
Meanwhile, Polly's crazy ass

00:27.038 --> 00:28.893
thought her dead twin sister came back,

00:28.895 --> 00:31.207
so Polly checked herself
into the nuthouse.

00:31.231 --> 00:32.542
I'm okay.

00:32.566 --> 00:34.745
Roller swore Uncle Daddy
killed his parents.

00:35.836 --> 00:37.347
Did you kill my dad?

00:37.371 --> 00:39.616
Ruval and Zlata
were scheming behind Des' back.

00:39.640 --> 00:41.017
Once you're married,

00:41.041 --> 00:44.020
everything Desna has
will be community property.

00:44.044 --> 00:45.688
But she took care of them...

00:47.848 --> 00:49.692
...with a little help.

00:51.585 --> 00:55.098
But in the end,
my girl bossed up like a G.

00:55.122 --> 00:57.121
I promised Clint here a piece of the pie

00:57.123 --> 00:58.701
after we got things all squared away.

00:58.725 --> 01:00.303
No deal.

01:00.327 --> 01:02.238
And she got more than she bargained for.

01:02.262 --> 01:04.328
- You got a casino.
- Wait, what?

01:04.331 --> 01:05.730
I got a casino?

01:05.732 --> 01:07.577
What you are about to see
is a cautionary tale.

01:07.601 --> 01:09.045
Be careful what you wish for, y'all.

01:09.069 --> 01:12.237
Help me!

01:14.741 --> 01:16.719
Somebody help us, please!

01:16.743 --> 01:18.010
Help us!

01:19.480 --> 01:21.301
Help us!

01:21.325 --> 01:23.480
- Drive-by?
- She was shot outside of a casino.

01:23.504 --> 01:26.418
- Gunshot wound to the right temple.
- Call the O.R., get me neurosurgery.

01:26.442 --> 01:27.882
- Yes, Doctor.
- Virginia, you're gonna be fine.

01:27.906 --> 01:29.185
- We've got her now.
- Gonna be okay.

01:29.209 --> 01:30.955
- We'll do everything we can.
- Please!

01:32.000 --> 01:38.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:51.445 --> 01:53.023
Yo, Des.

01:53.047 --> 01:55.225
Des, hey. You okay?

01:55.249 --> 01:56.382
Yeah.

01:57.918 --> 01:59.896
Dean, I am so sorry.

01:59.920 --> 02:02.365
They were aiming for me,
and then Virginia stepped in front...

02:02.389 --> 02:04.300
From... From what you said
about her injuries,

02:04.324 --> 02:07.170
uh, Virginia has a 23.8% chance
of dying, Des.

02:07.194 --> 02:10.773
23.8% chance. I looked it up on the way.

02:10.797 --> 02:12.242
Who do you think tried to 86 you,

02:12.266 --> 02:13.598
the Russian or the Haitian?

02:13.600 --> 02:14.977
I don't know.

02:15.001 --> 02:17.914
It could be somebody we don't even know.

02:17.938 --> 02:19.804
Roller, I need you to help me find out.

02:19.806 --> 02:23.042
Hey, D, I got you. Okay?

02:24.670 --> 02:27.524
Virginia... she could die because of me.

02:27.839 --> 02:30.593
They could come after me,
and my whole crew is in danger.

02:39.159 --> 02:41.738
I love that suit.

02:41.762 --> 02:42.939
Hmm.

02:42.963 --> 02:44.674
What else do we know about her?

02:47.434 --> 02:50.747
A fair amount, thanks to good Dr. Ruval.

02:50.771 --> 02:53.750
Washes money from
a Dixie Mafia pain clinic

02:53.774 --> 02:55.418
through her salon.

02:55.442 --> 02:58.355
But then things went south
when the Russians got involved.

02:58.379 --> 02:59.890
Oh, that's right.

02:59.914 --> 03:03.159
Ruval was hanging out with that
crazy Russian chick.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.562
Could never understand a thing
that messy whore was saying.

03:05.586 --> 03:07.097
I'm glad they're both dead.

03:07.121 --> 03:09.966
- You think Desna killed them?
- Don't know.

03:09.990 --> 03:14.571
Either way, she's trouble,
and we don't need trouble.

03:14.595 --> 03:16.172
Mm.

03:16.555 --> 03:19.576
Not that kind of trouble, anyway.

03:21.201 --> 03:24.955
We should go by with flowers.

03:25.686 --> 03:27.306
Oh, that's the least we can do.

03:29.075 --> 03:32.054
- Ohh.
- Ohh.

03:46.092 --> 03:49.205
And the year after that,
I bought the new model.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.895
John Deere 3000.

03:50.897 --> 03:53.898
She is a beauty.

03:53.900 --> 03:56.813
Mows real precise.

03:56.837 --> 03:58.102
Down to 1 1/2 inches.

03:58.104 --> 04:01.418
Hell, 1 inch if you like.

04:01.442 --> 04:04.220
You can borrow it any time
if you like it. Mm-hmm.

04:04.603 --> 04:06.812
Sounds like a jamboree.

04:08.106 --> 04:11.161
So, uh, Becky, have long have
you been running Sexy Tips?

04:11.185 --> 04:12.362
About eight years.

04:12.386 --> 04:13.430
- Wow.
- Mm-hmm.

04:13.454 --> 04:15.832
- And you are gonna fit right in.
- Oh!

04:15.856 --> 04:17.300
Oh, my goodness.

04:17.324 --> 04:20.101
- Look at your nails.
- Well...

04:20.125 --> 04:21.772
Oh, we're going to see
the Queen B. tomorrow.

04:21.796 --> 04:23.015
Whoa.

04:23.039 --> 04:24.308
- Drop it.
- Baby.

04:24.332 --> 04:25.308
Baby, you're gonna hurt him.

04:25.332 --> 04:26.531
Baby, don't put the hurt on him.

04:26.533 --> 04:27.732
We don't know them like that.

04:27.734 --> 04:29.179
Baby!

04:29.203 --> 04:31.448
Look out. Wow.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.850
But you might want to

04:33.874 --> 04:36.140
tone down your acrylics just...

04:36.299 --> 04:38.011
- Oh, no.
- Excuse me?

04:38.035 --> 04:40.480
They're just a little, mm, urban?

04:40.504 --> 04:44.151
Oh, you might want to back up,
Becky with the good hair.

04:44.175 --> 04:46.908
What? N... I am not racist...

04:46.910 --> 04:48.021
- No way.
- ...girlfriend.

04:48.045 --> 04:50.958
I love that Ben Carson.

04:50.982 --> 04:52.292
Nah, he's a good one.

04:52.316 --> 04:54.093
- Condoleezza Rice.
- We call her Condi.

04:54.117 --> 04:55.428
Stacey Dash.

04:55.452 --> 04:57.697
- She is practically one of us now.
- Practically?

04:57.721 --> 04:58.698
Will you excuse me?

04:58.722 --> 05:00.099
I have to alert the gas company

05:00.123 --> 05:01.657
about a potential leak.

05:04.996 --> 05:06.974
Des, you got to save me.

05:06.998 --> 05:08.308
Tell me something filthy.

05:08.332 --> 05:10.109
Jenn, I'ma have to call you back, okay?

05:10.133 --> 05:11.911
V-Virginia's in the hospital right now.

05:11.935 --> 05:12.934
What, why?

05:12.936 --> 05:14.603
- She got shot.
- Shot?!

05:16.273 --> 05:17.584
Okay, I'm on my way.

05:17.608 --> 05:20.520
No, no, no, no.
Please do not come here, okay?

05:20.544 --> 05:22.990
Everybody is still in danger.

05:23.014 --> 05:24.924
I'ma call you back.

05:27.284 --> 05:28.928
What about Zlata's daughter, Olga?

05:28.952 --> 05:30.330
I don't know. What about her?

05:30.354 --> 05:32.265
I mean, we weren't
exactly Oprah and Gayle,

05:32.289 --> 05:33.733
but I don't think this little girl

05:33.757 --> 05:35.468
would try to shoot at me
in broad daylight.

05:35.492 --> 05:38.159
So, who else would want to kill you?
I don't know.

05:38.161 --> 05:39.539
Well, what about the Dixie Mafia?

05:39.563 --> 05:41.963
Uncle Daddy felt a way
when he lost the pill mill,

05:41.965 --> 05:45.078
but... And I just inherited a casino.

05:45.102 --> 05:46.279
Maybe somebody from there.

05:46.303 --> 05:47.814
Well, until we figure it out,

05:47.838 --> 05:49.349
we're gonna put a
security detail on your house.

05:49.373 --> 05:51.172
No, no. I can handle it.

05:51.174 --> 05:52.419
Don't be stupid, Desna.

05:52.443 --> 05:53.620
If you're gonna take this on yourself,

05:53.644 --> 05:55.672
I can't help you this time.

05:56.298 --> 05:58.358
- Hey!
- Hey, yourself.

05:58.382 --> 06:00.427
Is Virginia gonna be alright?

06:00.451 --> 06:01.761
We don't know yet.

06:01.785 --> 06:03.162
I should have been there.

06:03.186 --> 06:05.032
No, no. It's not your fault.

06:05.056 --> 06:06.700
Well, I'm not going anywhere. Good.

06:06.724 --> 06:09.168
Listen, I need you to keep
an eye on Virginia's room.

06:09.192 --> 06:12.239
The shooter could come back.

06:28.879 --> 06:31.012
Why are you giving this to me?

06:31.014 --> 06:34.015
Because you have nothing to say.

06:44.361 --> 06:47.228
I have some good news.
Virginia's gonna make it.

06:47.230 --> 06:48.541
Oh, thank God.

06:48.565 --> 06:50.763
The bullet didn't penetrate the cranium,

06:50.787 --> 06:53.172
- but it did affect her eye.
- What?

06:53.196 --> 06:56.539
She had a corneal transplant
from an elderly Reiki healer.

07:02.045 --> 07:03.423
Domino!

07:03.447 --> 07:05.825
Now, that's how you throw bones, pussies!

07:05.849 --> 07:06.886
What, what!

07:06.910 --> 07:08.428
You have a phone call, Polly.

07:08.452 --> 07:10.297
Phone call? Ooh.

07:10.321 --> 07:12.454
I'll take it on the white courtesy phone

07:12.456 --> 07:13.767
in the Flamingo Room.

07:13.791 --> 07:17.258
For the last time, it's just a pay phone.

07:17.260 --> 07:18.661
Killjoy.

07:20.664 --> 07:22.263
- Hello?
- Hey, Polly. It's Ann.

07:22.265 --> 07:25.178
- Hey, what's up, Ann?
- Virginia's in the hospital.

07:25.202 --> 07:26.263
What?

07:28.052 --> 07:31.585
Square dancing's over!
Under new management.

07:31.609 --> 07:34.854
How you livin', Uncle?

07:36.832 --> 07:38.218
Well... good to see you, boy.

07:38.525 --> 07:40.682
About a million ways
I can answer that question.

07:40.684 --> 07:44.854
Number one, I'm living on a cot
in the Messianic Jewish Center.

07:45.323 --> 07:47.391
Number two, I'm about
running out of whiskey.

07:47.415 --> 07:49.660
Was it you who tried to kill Desna?

07:49.684 --> 07:51.483
What are you talking about?

07:51.485 --> 07:53.263
Someone tried to take out Desna?

07:53.287 --> 07:55.876
Yeah, a couple of hours ago
in front of the casino.

07:56.290 --> 07:58.469
Well, I was at Toucan's.

07:58.493 --> 08:00.404
Power tops drink for free on Friday.

08:00.428 --> 08:01.939
Clay, you stay lyin', man.

08:01.963 --> 08:03.541
Think I don't know you're not happy

08:03.565 --> 08:04.957
with the way things end up with Desna?

08:04.959 --> 08:06.811
Hey, I ain't lyin'.

08:06.835 --> 08:08.478
And we both know
why you really pissed off.

08:08.502 --> 08:09.613
Why is that?

08:09.637 --> 08:11.015
Well, 'cause you think
I killed your folks.

08:11.039 --> 08:13.083
I ain't got no time for thinkin'.

08:13.107 --> 08:14.418
I know.

08:14.442 --> 08:16.020
Yeah, you don't know shit.

08:16.044 --> 08:18.648
If I wanted Desna dead, she'd be dead.

08:22.851 --> 08:25.196
The Toucan shit don't add up...

08:26.113 --> 08:27.782
I'ma end you, Clay.

08:29.457 --> 08:31.301
- Hey, oh.
- Watch out, Springsteen.

08:32.727 --> 08:34.772
Things seem tense.

08:34.796 --> 08:36.640
Yeah, 'cause of you.

08:36.664 --> 08:38.842
- What did I do?
- What'd you do?

08:38.866 --> 08:40.644
Tried to convince him I killed his daddy.

08:41.936 --> 08:44.507
Now he thinks I tried to kill Desna, too.

08:46.007 --> 08:48.219
You wouldn't know anything
about that, would you?

08:49.010 --> 08:51.056
I ain't saying I shot her,

08:51.479 --> 08:53.746
but I do know karma's a bitch.

09:01.756 --> 09:03.276
Yes, it is.

09:08.096 --> 09:11.598
Paging Dr. Ross. Dr. Ross to the O.R.

09:15.770 --> 09:17.147
- Desna Simms?
- Yes?

09:17.171 --> 09:18.482
I'm Mac Lovestone.

09:18.506 --> 09:21.886
And this is my beautiful
and intelligent wife, Melba.

09:21.910 --> 09:23.353
So very nice to meet you.

09:23.377 --> 09:24.688
Okay.

09:24.712 --> 09:27.291
We just wish
the circumstances were brighter.

09:34.055 --> 09:36.834
20 years of cigs will get you eventually.

09:36.858 --> 09:38.769
I-I'm sorry. Who are you?

09:38.793 --> 09:40.504
We were your husband's partners

09:40.528 --> 09:43.708
over at Bayside Rapture Hotel & Casino.

09:43.732 --> 09:45.576
I didn't know Gregory had partners.

09:45.600 --> 09:47.712
I thought he owned the whole thing,

09:47.736 --> 09:50.047
meaning I own the whole thing.

09:50.071 --> 09:51.982
- Oh.
- Oh, no.

09:52.006 --> 09:53.451
You... You were mistaken.

09:53.475 --> 09:55.119
Bayside is a Native casino,

09:55.143 --> 09:58.522
and by law, non-Natives can
only be minority stakeholders.

09:58.546 --> 09:59.746
Huh.

10:01.015 --> 10:05.195
Oh, I have a little
Native American inside me.

10:05.219 --> 10:06.931
Every night around 9:30.

10:06.955 --> 10:09.800
Who you calling little? I'm 5'11".

10:09.824 --> 10:11.335
You are. You are a big man.

10:11.359 --> 10:12.403
Ohh. You're a big man.

10:12.427 --> 10:14.204
Thank you, baby.

10:14.228 --> 10:16.406
Wha...

10:16.430 --> 10:20.144
We'd just like to give you back
Greg's stake in the casino.

10:20.168 --> 10:22.613
That way, you can start
your process of healing

10:22.637 --> 10:25.105
after your tragic loss.

10:26.975 --> 10:28.503
$50,000?

10:28.527 --> 10:30.196
You deserve it.

10:31.379 --> 10:34.092
Yeah, well, I...

10:34.116 --> 10:38.851
I'ma need a little time
to process all of this.

10:38.853 --> 10:40.965
My friend has just been shot.

10:40.989 --> 10:42.767
If I were you, I would just take it.

10:42.791 --> 10:44.168
Just walk away

10:44.192 --> 10:46.370
and wash your hands of the whole mess.

10:46.394 --> 10:47.994
Well... Whoa.

10:49.664 --> 10:51.121
Okay.

10:51.145 --> 10:53.333
Okay. We're good.

10:55.670 --> 10:57.315
Enjoy this bounty.

11:12.285 --> 11:13.618
50,000...

11:13.754 --> 11:15.154
- Shh, shh, shh, shh.
- ...dollars?

11:15.156 --> 11:17.334
You know how many jumpsuits
you could buy with this?

11:17.358 --> 11:19.270
Yeah, but I don't just want the jumpsuit.

11:19.294 --> 11:21.939
I want the purse and the shoes to match.

11:21.963 --> 11:24.141
They ain't gettin' rid of me this easy.

11:24.165 --> 11:27.144
I don't know, Des.
They seem sketchy to me.

11:27.168 --> 11:29.414
I-I say just take the money and run.

11:29.438 --> 11:33.550
But the casino could take our
game to a whole nother level.

11:33.574 --> 11:36.754
That's what I'm talking about.

11:36.778 --> 11:37.888
Roller.

11:37.912 --> 11:39.556
It wasn't Uncle Daddy.

11:39.580 --> 11:40.625
It wasn't Uncle Daddy.

11:40.649 --> 11:42.427
What about the Haitians or the Russians?

11:42.451 --> 11:44.561
- I talked to everybody.
- Shit.

11:44.585 --> 11:47.965
Look, this creepy Native American guy

11:47.989 --> 11:50.100
and his golfer lady wife came over here,

11:50.124 --> 11:52.169
throwing around a fat-ass check.

11:52.193 --> 11:53.971
Maybe they the ones
that tried to kill me.

11:53.995 --> 11:55.906
Hey, D, I got a little
connect at the casino.

11:55.930 --> 11:57.196
My boy works security,

11:57.198 --> 11:58.709
so I could do a little digging around.

11:58.733 --> 12:00.110
- I got this.
- Okay, good.

12:00.134 --> 12:01.912
Anything you can do, Roller.

12:01.936 --> 12:04.195
We got a target on our backs.

12:04.219 --> 12:06.183
I got you, D.

12:11.946 --> 12:14.125
Time for your meds.

12:14.149 --> 12:15.392
Here you go.

12:15.416 --> 12:16.661
Thank you.

12:16.685 --> 12:18.885
Down the hatch.

12:21.890 --> 12:24.001
Ahh, ahh, ahh.

12:24.025 --> 12:25.424
Good girl.

12:25.426 --> 12:27.826
I'm just gonna have an early evening,

12:27.828 --> 12:29.540
so I don't need any turndown service,

12:29.564 --> 12:31.097
but thank you.

12:46.447 --> 12:47.847
Oh!

12:47.849 --> 12:49.827
Shit.

12:49.851 --> 12:50.895
Polly!

12:50.919 --> 12:51.962
Huh?

12:51.986 --> 12:53.252
No, no, unh-unh.

12:53.254 --> 12:54.365
You're not gonna stop me.

12:54.389 --> 12:56.701
I won't be defined by my diagnosis.

12:56.725 --> 12:58.769
It's a voluntary ward.

12:58.793 --> 13:02.773
If you want to go, you can
walk out the front door.

13:02.797 --> 13:04.375
Good to know.

13:04.399 --> 13:05.465
Some help?

13:08.136 --> 13:10.647
Yo. So, how dirty are these casino folks?

13:10.671 --> 13:11.871
Killin' dirty?

13:11.873 --> 13:13.450
Who I look like, "Murder, She Wrote"?

13:13.474 --> 13:16.675
They dirty, like Flint water dirty.

13:16.677 --> 13:18.322
Yeah, but they mobbed up?

13:18.346 --> 13:20.057
I swear it...

13:24.419 --> 13:26.731
Go ask 'em your damn self.

13:26.755 --> 13:28.533
Seatbelts, please.

13:28.557 --> 13:29.734
This is gonna be fun!

13:41.302 --> 13:44.749
Please, no.

13:46.507 --> 13:48.085
Please. No, please.

13:50.044 --> 13:54.358
No, no, no. Wait, wait, wait.
No, no, no! No, no, please!

13:54.382 --> 13:55.915
No, no, no, no, no, please, please!

13:55.917 --> 13:57.494
Please, please, please, please!

13:57.518 --> 14:01.498
Then do what we need you to do
and stay in your place.

14:01.522 --> 14:03.167
Okay! Okay, okay, okay, okay!

14:03.191 --> 14:04.701
I'll back off! I promise!

14:04.725 --> 14:06.837
That's great.

14:06.861 --> 14:08.639
We'll see you at work Monday.

14:08.663 --> 14:11.730
And I don't want to see these
two hours on your timecard.

14:21.476 --> 14:23.454
Oh, thank God Virginia's okay.

14:23.478 --> 14:25.456
I knew our girl would pull through.

14:25.480 --> 14:28.926
Polly, I had no idea
you could cook soul food.

14:28.950 --> 14:31.150
What are you, like an octoroon?

14:31.152 --> 14:32.329
Well, you know,

14:32.353 --> 14:34.131
my family doesn't like to talk about it,

14:34.155 --> 14:36.267
but we've been
passing for white for years.

14:36.291 --> 14:38.335
- Girl, shut up.
- No, it's true.

14:38.359 --> 14:41.961
Patti LaBelle's cousin's cousin
is my cousin!

14:41.963 --> 14:43.340
You should taste my sweet potato pie,

14:43.364 --> 14:45.139
and then you'd know for sure. Mm-hmm.

14:45.163 --> 14:47.077
I'm just glad you're out of the nuthouse.

14:47.101 --> 14:48.946
Well, I'm not really out out.

14:48.970 --> 14:50.281
I'm still on crazy parole.

14:50.305 --> 14:53.951
Regular medication checks,
weekly psychotherapy,

14:53.975 --> 14:55.374
group sessions on Sundays.

14:55.376 --> 14:56.553
Can you believe that? Eeh.

14:56.577 --> 14:58.155
But no more Lillian, right?

14:58.179 --> 15:00.272
No, no, just me.

15:01.516 --> 15:04.094
- Mm! Hey, Deanie.
- Hey.

15:04.118 --> 15:06.363
I didn't know, um, you were coming here.

15:06.387 --> 15:07.564
You want me to fix you a plate?

15:07.588 --> 15:08.966
No, I'm... I'm just here to pick up

15:08.990 --> 15:10.501
some of my... of my... my clothes.

15:10.525 --> 15:12.569
- How did you get over here?
- The bus.

15:12.593 --> 15:14.171
You got to be careful, Dean.

15:14.195 --> 15:16.774
Listen to me.
The people who tried to kill me

15:16.798 --> 15:19.243
could easily come after
the people that I love, baby.

15:19.267 --> 15:21.111
We can't take them kind of chances.

15:21.135 --> 15:24.003
It's okay. I'm... I'm okay.

15:24.005 --> 15:25.916
I can handle myself.

15:25.940 --> 15:27.184
Dean, listen...

15:27.208 --> 15:28.407
I-I'm just gonna pick up my stuff,

